column5: Anyone been out in the past few days?  I'm debating making the hour and a half trip. I've heard its been really slow for the past while, but wondering if its picked up at all?  Cheers, *Stoty
Where have you been man? Jim
Back in school now.......takes up most of my time.  I'd love to get out today and break the 10lb mark!
Stoty Will you be there this week?? I'll be there for the next 4 days. Leaving in the morning

Stoty, Im heading there tomorrow till sunday on my yearly pilgrimage to get some big eyes, I hope.  Probably won't sleep tonight cause i'm so excited, but lifes tough sometimes.haha. Hope to post some nice pics when I get back. Fish
I am hoping to get there Friday, Saturday or Sunday....maybe even a couple days!  Good luck guys!

hope this helps folks  thompsons point is still giving up nice eyes also up the reach towards deseronto has good reports as well,also east of the ferry in picton from what im hearing  is starting to heat up again,the eyes have moved in from a holding area out in lake O,they were putting on the feed bag sorta speak lol.  most are trolling but i only jig,don't be affraid of stopping the boat and start jigging if ya mark lots of eyes that are not hitting the troll,use your ice fishing spoons.  good luck to all and stay safe out there winds have been on the fishermens side the last little while so get out and enjoy what Quinte has to offer.  "OH" i seen a fair number of bows being boated as well  taker easy all  Hawg Hunter
